 Promises abound in the battle to lead the ANC in the Eastern Cape as the provincial conference gets underway. eNCA's Aviwe Mtila reports. #DStv403 GQEBERHA - Babalo Madikizela is contesting the Eastern Cape ANC chairmanship on a promise to redirect investment to the province. He's vying for the position held by a once-close ally, Lubabalo Oscar Mabuyane. READ: ANC Eastern Cape conference gets underway The provincial elective conference is expected to get into full swing on Saturday. Some members say Mabuyane has not done anything for the province. * eNCA's Aviwe Mtila reports.